\section{Introduction}

This minimal example demonstrates the font error that occurs in the QE submission build.

The problem: The \texttt{econsocart} document class defines subsections to use
\textbf{small caps + italic} (\texttt{scit}) font variant, but Utopia font
does not have this combination.

\section{The Error}

When you compile this document with pdflatex, you will see:

\begin{verbatim}
LaTeX Error: Font T1/put/m/scit/12 not found.
\end{verbatim}

This happens at the first subsection command:

\subsection{This Subsection Will Cause an Error}

The \texttt{econsocart} class tries to render this subsection title in
small caps + italic, but Utopia font (family code \texttt{put}) does
not have the \texttt{scit} variant defined.

\subsection{Another Failing Subsection}

Each subsection command will produce the same error.

\section{Why This Happens}

\begin{itemize}
  \item
        Utopia font has these variants separately:
        \begin{itemize}
          \item
                Normal: \textrm{Regular text}
          \item
                Bold: \textbf{Bold text}
          \item
                Italic: \textit{Italic text}
          \item
                Small caps: \textsc{Small Caps}
        \end{itemize}

  \item
        Utopia does NOT have these combinations:
        \begin{itemize}
          \item
                Small caps + italic (\texttt{scit})
          \item
                Small caps + slanted (\texttt{scsl})
        \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\section{To Reproduce the Error}

Compile this file:
\begin{verbatim}
pdflatex font-fix_problem.tex
\end{verbatim}

You will see the compilation fail when it encounters the first
\texttt{\textbackslash subsection} command.

\section{The Solution}

See \texttt{font-fix-solution.tex} for how to fix this issue.

